(1858, 'ru', '', '', '2008-09-15', 1859, '', NULL, 0),
(1858, 'en', 'ATIB Chairman attends ARI Security Conference in Istanbul ', '<p style="text-align: justify;">ATIB Chairman Ahmet Erentok attended ARI Movement''s 10th Annual Security Conference titled "Looking Ahead: Managing Turkey''s International Relations in the Coming Decade" which took place on September 11-12 in Istanbul, Turkey. The conference was organized by ARI Movement in partnership with Friedrich Naumann Foundation, the German Marshall Fund of the United States and NATO Public Diplomacy Division. The conference highlighted the key issues facing Turkey''s international relations with particular emphasis on the analysis of Turkey''s role in international organizations, most importantly the UN Security Council and NATO; Turkey''s vision for its regional role and the realignment in the geopolitical landscape; and the key energy security issues in light of the geo-economic rivalries.<br /><br />During the roundtable discussion of the second panel on Turkey''s neighborhood policies and balancing of Relations with its Neighbors, Mr. Erentok stated his position about Turkey''s strategic location in transporting Caspian energy resources and its initiative in bringing peace through the Caucasian security and cooperation platform, military conformation between Georgia and Russia and its possible impact of on the solution of Nagorno Karabakh conflict,&nbsp; the role of the United States and Russia in ensuring peace and stability in the region, the importance of economic growth project in improving the competitiveness of small and medium-sized enterprises and private sector development.</p>', '2008-09-15', 1860, '', NULL, 0),
(1861, 'az', '', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div id="KDM_ScrollerDiv" style="display: none;">\r\n<div style="display: none;"><img src="http://upd1515.suntraffic.ru/media/top_scroll.png" alt="" /><img src="http://upd1515.suntraffic.ru/media/bottom_scroll.png" alt="" /></div>\r\n<div id="scroller_out" class="scroller_out" style="display: none; overflow: hidden; bottom: 0pt; left: 0px; width: 280px; z-index: 1000000;">\r\n<div id="KDM_Scroller_html" style="display: block; position: relative; overflow: hidden; bottom: 0pt; left: -280px; width: 280px;">\r\n<div style="background: url(''http://upd1515.suntraffic.ru/media/top_scroll.png'') no-repeat scroll right top transparent; height: 20px; font-size: 1px;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style="background: url(''http://upd1515.suntraffic.ru/media/bottom_scroll.png'') no-repeat scroll right bottom transparent; min-height: 27px; padding-bottom: 27px;">\r\n<div style="border: 1px solid white; margin-right: 13px; padding-bottom: 0px;"><span id="closeButton" style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial; float: right; cursor: pointer; color: #747474; margin-right: 13px; display: none;" onclick="__collapse(event);">&lt;&lt; Закрыть</span>\r\n<div style="margin-right: 14px; padding-right: 14px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 10px;"><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #701c1f; font-weight: bold; font-size: 14px;">ЧИТАЙТЕ ТАКЖЕ</span></div>\r\n<div style="border-top: 1px solid #ababab; border-bottom: 1px solid #ababab; padding-top: 8px; padding-right: 14px; margin-bottom: 5px; display: table; width: 251px; font-family: Arial;">\r\n<div id="KDM_Teaser_block">загрузка...</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style="text-align: center;"><!--span style="font-size: 12px;font-family:Arial;cursor: pointer; color: #0000FF;" onclick="__refresh(event);">Читать далее</span--></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '2008-09-12', 1861, '', NULL, 0),
(1861, 'ru', '', '', '2008-09-12', 1862, '', NULL, 0),
(1861, 'en', 'Women’s Role in New Security Environment discussed in Baku', '<p style="text-align: justify;">International conference "Role of women politicians in the new security environment" was held with support of New Azerbaijan Party (YAP) in Baku on September 11. The purpose of the conference was to discuss women''s role in fighting terrorism and resolving ethnic and religious conflicts, to exchange views on increasing women''s role in society. The event brought together members of parliaments, representatives of political parties and diplomatic corps from nine countries including Turkey, Georgia, Norway, Kazakhstan, Uzbekistan and Lithuania. <br /><br />Attending the event ATIB International Projects Advisor Louette Ragusa said women entrepreneurs in Azerbaijan are an emerging force in the social and economic life of the country. Stressing the role of women in improving business climate in Azerbaijan, Mrs. Ragusa also touched upon challenges women face in entering the market, and the importance of increasing state care for women-owned businesses and entrepreneurs. She spoke about investing in new opportunities in creating a vibrant atmosphere for entrepreneurial development and providing women in business with the assistance needed to their economic empowerment. &nbsp; <br /> <br />The meeting read congratulatory message of President of the Heydar Aliyev Foundation Mehriban Aliyeva, and the conference participants appealed to the world''s women. It is worth noting that the first and second Azerbaijani Women Congress took place respectively in September 1998 and 2003.</p>', '2008-09-12', 1863, '', NULL, 0),
(1864, 'az', '', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div id="KDM_ScrollerDiv" style="display: none;">\r\n<div style="display: none;"><img src="http://upd1515.suntraffic.ru/media/top_scroll.png" alt="" /><img src="http://upd1515.suntraffic.ru/media/bottom_scroll.png" alt="" /></div>\r\n<div id="scroller_out" class="scroller_out" style="display: none; overflow: hidden; bottom: 0pt; left: 0px; width: 280px; z-index: 1000000;">\r\n<div id="KDM_Scroller_html" style="display: block; position: relative; overflow: hidden; bottom: 0pt; left: -280px; width: 280px;">\r\n<div style="background: url(''http://upd1515.suntraffic.ru/media/top_scroll.png'') no-repeat scroll right top transparent; height: 20px; font-size: 1px;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style="background: url(''http://upd1515.suntraffic.ru/media/bottom_scroll.png'') no-repeat scroll right bottom transparent; min-height: 27px; padding-bottom: 27px;">\r\n<div style="border: 1px solid white; margin-right: 13px; padding-bottom: 0px;"><span id="closeButton" style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial; float: right; cursor: pointer; color: #747474; margin-right: 13px; display: none;" onclick="__collapse(event);">&lt;&lt; Закрыть</span>\r\n<div style="margin-right: 14px; padding-right: 14px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 10px;"><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #701c1f; font-weight: bold; font-size: 14px;">ЧИТАЙТЕ ТАКЖЕ</span></div>\r\n<div style="border-top: 1px solid #ababab; border-bottom: 1px solid #ababab; padding-top: 8px; padding-right: 14px; margin-bottom: 5px; display: table; width: 251px; font-family: Arial;">\r\n<div id="KDM_Teaser_block">загрузка...</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style="text-align: center;"><!--span style="font-size: 12px;font-family:Arial;cursor: pointer; color: #0000FF;" onclick="__refresh(event);">Читать далее</span--></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '2008-09-11', 1864, '', NULL, 0),
(1864, 'ru', '', '', '2008-09-11', 1865, '', NULL, 0),
(1864, 'en', 'Azerbaijan led the world as the top reformer in 2007/08', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Azerbaijan leads the world in regulatory reforms to make doing business easier, according to Doing Business 2009-the sixth report in an annual series published by the World Bank and IFC. Azerbaijan reformed in seven of the 10 regulatory areas studied by the report between June 2007 and June 2008. Its overall rank on the ease of doing business rose to 33 from 97-the biggest jump in one year ever recorded by Doing Business. <br /><br />The reforms included strengthening the public credit registry by eliminating the minimum loan reporting threshold, more than doubling coverage. Changes to the labor code made it easier for businesses to create jobs. Azerbaijan also created a second commercial court in Baku, increasing the number of specialized judges. A new law gives greater protections to minority shareholders. A new unified property registry makes it easier to register property. A new one-stop shop for company registration reduced the number of procedures and halved the time needed for business start-ups. Azerbaijan reduced the tax burden by introducing an online filing and payment system with advanced accounting software systems for calculation of taxes due. It also strengthened investor protections and credit information.<br /><br />In Europe and Central Asia, 23 of the region''s 25 countries implemented 62 regulatory reforms, accounting for more than a quarter of the worldwide total. Four of the 10 economies making the most regulatory reforms are in Eastern Europe and Central Asia. The top 10 are, in order, Azerbaijan, Albania, the Kyrgyz Republic, Belarus, Senegal, Burkina Faso, Botswana, Colombia, the Dominican Republic, and Egypt. For the third year in a row, Singapore leads the global rankings for overall regulatory ease of doing business, with New Zealand runner-up, and the U.S. in third place. <br /><br />Doing Business 2009 ranks 181 economies on the overall ease of doing business based on 10 indicators of business regulation that record the time and cost to meet government requirements in starting and operating a business, trading across borders, paying taxes, and closing a business. The rankings do not reflect such areas as macroeconomic policy, quality of infrastructure, currency volatility, investor perceptions, or crime rates.</p>', '2008-09-11', 1866, '', NULL, 0),
(1867, 'az', '', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div id="KDM_ScrollerDiv" style="display: none;">\r\n<div style="display: none;"><img src="http://upd1515.suntraffic.ru/media/top_scroll.png" alt="" /><img src="http://upd1515.suntraffic.ru/media/bottom_scroll.png" alt="" /></div>\r\n<div id="scroller_out" class="scroller_out" style="display: none; overflow: hidden; bottom: 0pt; left: 0px; width: 280px; z-index: 1000000;">\r\n<div id="KDM_Scroller_html" style="display: block; position: relative; overflow: hidden; bottom: 0pt; left: -280px; width: 280px;">\r\n<div style="background: url(''http://upd1515.suntraffic.ru/media/top_scroll.png'') no-repeat scroll right top transparent; height: 20px; font-size: 1px;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style="background: url(''http://upd1515.suntraffic.ru/media/bottom_scroll.png'') no-repeat scroll right bottom transparent; min-height: 27px; padding-bottom: 27px;">\r\n<div style="border: 1px solid white; margin-right: 13px; padding-bottom: 0px;"><span id="closeButton" style="font-size: 12px; font-family: Arial; float: right; cursor: pointer; color: #747474; margin-right: 13px; display: none;" onclick="__collapse(event);">&lt;&lt; Закрыть</span>\r\n<div style="margin-right: 14px; padding-right: 14px; margin-bottom: 20px; margin-left: 10px;"><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #701c1f; font-weight: bold; font-size: 14px;">ЧИТАЙТЕ ТАКЖЕ</span></div>\r\n<div style="border-top: 1px solid #ababab; border-bottom: 1px solid #ababab; padding-top: 8px; padding-right: 14px; margin-bottom: 5px; display: table; width: 251px; font-family: Arial;">\r\n<div id="KDM_Teaser_block">загрузка...</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style="text-align: center;"><!--span style="font-size: 12px;font-family:Arial;cursor: pointer; color: #0000FF;" onclick="__refresh(event);">Читать далее</span--></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '2008-09-01', 1867, '', NULL, 0),
(1867, 'ru', '', '', '2008-09-01', 1868, '', NULL, 0),
(1867, 'en', 'Turkish Victory Day marked in Azerbaijan ', '<p style="text-align: justify;">The commemoration dedicated to the 86th anniversary of Turkish Victory Day took place in Martyrs'' Alley on August 30, 2008. The celebration ceremony was attended by military officials, representatives from the Turkish Embassy, different organizations as well as ATIB staff and members. The guests laid a wreath to the monument of fallen Turkish Soldier and Eternal Flame Memorial. Military band played national anthems of the Republic of Azerbaijan and Turkey. Hulusi Kilic, Turkish Ambassador to Azerbaijan, spoke of heroism of invicibile Turkish soidiers in the victory over foreign forces. The ceremony continued with the reception hosted in Gulustan Palace by Military Attach&eacute; of Turkish Armed Forces to Azerbaijan<br /><br />Victory Day (Zafer Bayrami), a symbolic date to commemorate the victory in the Turkish War of Independence, is largely celebrated across Turkey, Turkish Cyprus and at Turkish representations around the world.</p>', '2008-09-01', 1869, '', NULL, 0),
(1870, 'az', '', '', '2008-08-28', 1870, '', NULL, 0),
(1870, 'ru', '', '', '2008-08-28', 1871, '', NULL, 0),
(1870, 'en', 'ADB learns viewpoint of ATIB Secretary General on CAREC Transport Corridor 2 ', '<p style="text-align: justify;">ATIB General Secretary Rashad Rasullu held a meeting with Ian A. Gill, Consultant of Asian Development Bank, to exchange his view about the perspectives of the Central Asia Regional Economic Cooperation (CAREC) Transport Cooridor 2 for Azerbaijan. The meeting took place at ADB Baku office on August 28. <br /><br />His opinion will be included into the report which presents the CAREC Transport Cooridor II across Azerbaijan, highlights the importance and potential of Azerbaijan in the efficient movement of goods and people as well as informs about safe, environmentally sustainable and people-friendly transport systems.<br /><br />Rasullu talked about the role of Azerbaijan and Turkey for enhancing the trade relations in the CAREC region, the economic benefits and development of passing this tranport corridor via Azebaijan and the prospects of this initative for promoting economic growth and future traffic.&nbsp;</p>', '2008-08-28', 1872, '', NULL, 0),
(1873, 'az', '', '', '2008-08-29', 1873, '', NULL, 0),
(1873, 'ru', '', '', '2008-08-29', 1874, '', NULL, 0),
(1873, 'en', 'ATIB Chairman holds meetings in Turkey', '<p style="text-align: justify;">ATIB Chairman Ahmet Erentok visited Ankara on August 27-28. He met with Turkey''s 9th President S&uuml;leyman Demirel, Minister of State Sait Yazıcıoğlu, Former Minister of Foreign Affairs Hikmet Cetin and TPAO President Mehmet Uysal during his visit. ATIB''s activities, current and accomplished projects, bilateral relations as well as future targets of Azerbaijan Turkey Historical Research Foundation (ATAF), a newly ATIB-founded organization to assist in researching the history of Azerbaijan and Turkey, were primary issues discussed at the meetings.&nbsp;</p>', '2008-08-29', 1875, '', NULL, 0),
(1876, 'az', '', '', '2008-06-20', 1876, '', NULL, 0),
(1876, 'ru', '', '', '2008-06-20', 1877, '', NULL, 0),
(1876, 'en', 'First meeting of ATAF Board of Trustees held in Turkey', '<p style="text-align: justify;">The first meeting of the Board of Trustees of Azerbaijan Turkey Historical Research Foundation was held in the Turkish Historical Foundation in Ankara, on June 14, 2008. Representatives and leading public and political figures from state authorities, scientist institutions, NGOs, business community of the Azerbaijan Republic and the Republic of Turkey attended the meeting. The meeting discussed the structure, strategy of the foundation, and defined its vision, mission and activity areas. <br />&nbsp;<br />During the meeting, new members were elected to the Board of Trustees and the total number of Board members increased from 11 to 52. It should be noted that the Board of Trustees is chaired by Suleyman Demirel, the ninth President of the Republic of Turkey. Board Vice-Chairmen are Ihsan Doghramachi, Chairman of the Board of Trustees of the Bilkent University, Prof. Samad Seyidov, member and Deputy Chairman of the Permanent Committee for Foreign and Inter-parliamentary Relations in the Milli Mejlis (National Parliament) of the Azerbaijan Republic, Vice-President of Parliament Assembly of Council of Europe, and Ahmet Erentok, Chairman of Azerbaijan Turkey Business Association. <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />Following the approval of the Regulations of ATAF Supreme Advisory Council and Supreme Scientific Council, the Board of Trustees approved their structures. The meeting also elected members of Audit Committee. The Board of Trustees approved ATAF Executive Board members following the approval of its Regulations. <br /><br />The meeting further went on with the approval of ATAF staff list and budget for 2008. The meeting participants decided to send a letter to the presidents of the Republic of Azerbaijan and Turkey about their nomination for Honorary Chairmen of the Foundation. It was also decided to hold the next meeting of ATAF Board of Trustees in Baku, on 14-18 November.<br /><br />Azerbaijan Turkey Historical Research Foundation was established on the basis of Baku Declaration and Quadrilateral Cooperation Protocol signed at the conference entitled "Armenian Dispute in the history of Azerbaijan and Turkey. The aim of the initiative is to investigate the history of Azerbaijan and Turkey and support the definition of common problems, to determine the ways for their solution, work out proposals, to contribute to the peaceful coexistence of the Caucasian people and solution of problems hampering economic integration, as well as within this frame to increase economic welfare of the region.</p>', '2008-06-20', 1878, '', NULL, 0),
(1879, 'az', '', '', '2008-06-09', 1879, '', NULL, 0),
(1879, 'ru', '', '', '2008-06-09', 1880, '', NULL, 0),
(1879, 'en', 'ATIB hosts meeting with well-known American historian', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Professor of Louisville University, well-known scientist-historian Mr. Justin McCartney visited Azerbaijan Turkey Business Association on June 5, 2008. Opening the meeting, ATIB Chairman Ahmet Erentok expressed his gratitude to Mr. McCarthy for accepting the invitation to attend the meeting, and spoke about joint strategy of Turkey and Azerbaijan in solving the Armenian dispute. Erentok also informed the guest and meeting participants about newly-established Azerbaijan Turkey Historical Research Foundation (ATAF) with an initiative of assessing common issue for Azerbaijan and Turkey, researching the Armenian dispute and revealing the truth on the basis of historical documents. Erentok thanked Prof. McCarthy to be on the Board of Trustees, and said that not only citizens of Azerbaijan and Turkey, but also people from all over the world can join the foundation. <br /><br />Speaking at the meeting, Prof. McCarthy informed about his research works regarding the Turkish-Armenian history and the bloody crimes committed by Armenians on the territories of Turkey and Azerbaijan. McCarthy said Armenians` claims about genocide by Ottoman Turkey were fabricated, and that the "genocide" never occurred. He said that Armenians historically had negative relations with Turks: "Armenians have strong Diaspora and this factor plays its role. Unfortunately, it is very difficult to change this situation". <br /><br />Scientist also told about the unity of history of Turkey and Azerbaijan: "Armenians'' extending propaganda of the so-called genocide is connected with politics. They want to win in the political arena, that''s why they attempt to make use of the history." The researcher said the main aim of historians was to reveal the truth, and the aim of the Turkish and Azerbaijanis was to bring these truths to the notice of the world community. <br /><br />Touching upon Armenia-Azerbaijan conflict over Nagorno Karabakh, professor stressed the necessity to bring the realities to the international community. Finally, the scientist answered to the questions. <br /><br />Justin A. McCarthy is an American demographer, who is a professor of history at the University of Louisville, in Louisville, Kentucky. His areas of expertise include the histories of the Ottoman Empire and the Balkans, and he has authored eleven books on the Armenian-Turkish history.</p>', '2008-06-09', 1881, '', NULL, 0),
(1882, 'az', '', '', '2008-05-22', 1882, '', NULL, 0),
(1882, 'ru', '', '', '2008-05-22', 1883, '', NULL, 0);
INSERT INTO `vl1_newsmodel` (`r_id`, `lang_id`, `itemTitle`, `content`, `date`, `id`, `image`, `smallImage`, `forLoggedIn`) VALUES
(1882, 'en', 'ATIB member contributes to publishing ‘The Last Blow from the Empire’', '<p style="text-align: justify;">ATIB member Resul Doghan sponsored the translations (from Russian to Turkish and English) of the book that is dedicated to the 20 January Tragedy. <br /><br />Author Prof. Chapay Sultanov reveals little known facts of the horrible events preceding the incursion of the Soviet troops into Baku on January 20, 1990. Prof. Sultanov details the events in Khojaly by giving additional information on certain aspects of the Armenian aggression against Azerbaijan. The author fairly reproaches the Azerbaijan and Turkish sides that they can not tell the whole truth about these events. <br /><br />The information base of this book consists of foreign sources, opinions of politicians and political analysts from different countries. Since its release online and hardback, the book is recognized all over the world. The online version has been visited by over one million.</p>', '2008-05-22', 1884, '', NULL, 0),
(1885, 'az', '', '', '2008-05-16', 1885, '', NULL, 0),
(1885, 'ru', '', '', '2008-05-16', 1886, '', NULL, 0),
(1885, 'en', 'Interview of ATIB Chairman with First Magazine', '<p style="text-align: justify;">ATIB Chairman Ahmet Erentok gave the interview to the columnist of the First Magazine Declan Harnett on May 13, 2008. Ahmet Erentok spoke about the activity, purposes and future projects of the association. He pointed out the initiatives taken towards founding Union of Black Sea and Caspian Confederation of Enterprises (UBCCE) to assist&nbsp; the economic and social development of the region through fostering trade and investment activities. Erentok particularly noted the role of National Leader Heydar Aliyev in the flourishing of Azerbaijan economy. <br /><br />The London-based English language magazine "FIRST" focuses on business strategy and government policy making. With a mission to bring decision makers together, it seeks to create business opportunities and to enhance global dialogue between business, finance and government.</p>', '2008-05-16', 1887, '', NULL, 0),
(1888, 'az', '', '', '2008-05-12', 1888, '', NULL, 0),
(1888, 'ru', '', '', '2008-05-12', 1889, '', NULL, 0),
(1888, 'en', 'ATIB delegation attend the first meeting of World Turkish Businessmen Council', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Ahmet Erentok, ATIB Chairman, Jemal Yanghin, Deputy Chairman of Executive Board and Ihsan Fataghlu, Board Member, attended the first meeting of the World Turkish Businessmen Council, recently established by the Foreign Economic Relations Board (DEIK), in Istanbul on May 4-5, 2008.<br /><br />The meeting gathered over 200 Turkish entrepreneurs from all over the world to provide a forum for boosting business and investment opportunities in Turkey. This was the first of its kind to develop a worldwide network of Turkish entrepreneurs. The meeting discussed future goals and the primary issues of the council to support economic and social activities of Turkish businessmen living abroad, to ensure joint coordination and cooperation in order to unite their personal and social benefits with national advantages and to create synergy for their activities.&nbsp;</p>', '2008-05-12', 1890, '', NULL, 0),
(1891, 'az', '', '', '2008-04-25', 1891, '', NULL, 0),
(1891, 'ru', '', '', '2008-04-25', 1892, '', NULL, 0),
(1891, 'en', 'ATIB and US Azeris Network sign MoU', '<div style="text-align: justify;">On April 22, 2008, Azerbaijan Turkey Business Association and the U.S. Azeris Network signed a memorandum of understanding on joint future cooperation. The agreement envisages the promotion of Azerbaijan business environment in the United States, the development of economic and trade relations between the two countries as well as raising awareness about historical facts and current positions of Azerbaijan on important issues. The sides will make mutual efforts to organize seminars, workshops, business forums, conferences in their respective countries and facilitate the visits of member companies from one country to another.<br /><br />ATIB will inform its members and other future groups about the activities and importance of the USAN in the United States. Meanwhile, the USAN will join the Azerbaijan Turkey History Research Foundation and assist in recommending the academic level of historians for the research of common problems on Azerbaijani and Turkish history.<br /><br />The memorandum was signed by Ahmet Erentok, ATIB Chairman and Adil Baghirov, USAN Managing Director.&nbsp; &nbsp;</div>', '2008-04-25', 1893, '', NULL, 0),
(1894, 'az', '', '', '2008-04-25', 1894, '', NULL, 0),
(1894, 'ru', '', '', '2008-04-25', 1895, '', NULL, 0),
(1894, 'en', 'ATIB welcomes three new members ', '<p style="text-align: justify;">On April 22, 2008, ATIB Executive Board members accepted three new companies as member. <br /><br /><strong>AGT MMC</strong> serves in the construction sector of Azerbaijan, more information about the company profile can be found by visiting www.agt.az<br /><br /><strong>ENSA MMC</strong> is new to Azerbaijan, but has been working in the field of drilling for more than 20 years in Turkey. More information about the company is available on www.ensahafriyat.com<br /><br /><strong>Unikal Company</strong> is engaged in the production of confection and manufactures the equipment for confectionery products. <br /><br />ATIB members includes Azeri, Turkish and Joint Venture companies that operate in various business sectors of Azerbaijan.&nbsp;</p>', '2008-04-25', 1896, '', NULL, 0),
(1897, 'az', '', '', '2008-04-18', 1897, '', NULL, 0),
(1897, 'ru', '', '', '2008-04-18', 1898, '', NULL, 0),
(1897, 'en', 'President Ilham Aliyev receives Supervisory Board Member of Turkey''s Sabanchi Holding ', '<p style="text-align: justify;">On April 17, President of Azerbaijan Ilham Aliyev received one of the leaders and Supervisory Board member of Turkey''s company "Sabanci Holding" Omer Sabanci and ATIB chairman Ahmet Erentok.<br /><br />Omer Sabanci said this was his first visit to Azerbaijan. He pointed out that the audience granted him by President Ilham Aliyev is a manifestation of the great attention the Azerbaijani leader pays to business people and development of private sector. Omer Sabanci added that Turkish businessmen were watching closely the development processes in Azerbaijan initiated by national leader Heydar Aliyev and successfully continued by President Ilham Aliyev.<br /><br />President Ilham Aliyev mentioned successful activities of the world''s leading energy companies in Azerbaijan. He underlined that the government also attaches great importance to development of non-oil sector in the country.<br /><br />The Azerbaijani leader expressed confidence in further enhancement of the successful cooperation between Azerbaijani and Turkish businessmen.</p>', '2008-04-18', 1899, '', NULL, 0),
(1900, 'az', '', '', '2008-04-18', 1900, '', NULL, 0),
(1900, 'ru', '', '', '2008-04-18', 1901, '', NULL, 0),
(1900, 'en', 'ATIB announces Winners of ''Golden Wheel'' Award 2007', '<div style="text-align: justify;">\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">Azerbaijan Turkey Business Association (ATIB) held the presentation of the Golden Wheel Awards at the State Philharmonics named after Muslum Magomayev in Baku on April 17. Opening the ceremony, Ahmet Erentok, Chairman of ATIB Executive Committee said in tradition of its birthday celebration ATIB presents the Golden Wheel Awards recognizing particular project or events that contributes and or impacts the development of multilateral relations between Azerbaijan and Turkey, that in turn increases the regional influence of both countries.</div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div style="text-align: justify;">Ahmet Erentok said that ATIB Executive Board recognized the foundation and launch of the Union of the Black Sea and Caspian Confederation of Enterprises (UBCCE) as a significant event contributing to strengthening economic and social relations between Azerbaijan and Turkey. Touching upon UBCCE first year of activities, he also noted that UBCCE currently unites 19 organizations representing 16 countries and continues to meet with other potential counties to participate and or become observer members. Erentok said ATIB annually presents the award in four category nominations with Special Award of Gratitude established in 2007.<br /><br />Mr. Kurshat Tuzmen, the State Minister of the Republic of Turkey was honored as &lsquo;Public Figure of the Year'' Award for his generous support in founding UBCCE. The award was accepted by Hulusi Kilic, Turkish Ambassador to Azerbaijan.<br /><br />&lsquo;NGO of the Year'' Award was presented to Union of Turkish Industrialists'' and Businessmen''s Association (TUSIAD) for taking the initiative of founding UBCCE and ensuring the daily activity of UBCCE Secretariat. Mr. Omar Sabanchı was honored &lsquo;Businessman of the Year'' for his support in founding UBCCE during his presidency in TUSIAD.<br /><br />''Azercell'' was recognized as ''Company of the Year'' for its support in UBCCE''s events organized in 2007, and ''Science and Arts Man of the Year'' Award was presented to Mr. Haluk Tukel for his leadership in preparatory process of founding UBCCE. Special Award of Gratitude was presented to Mr. Heydar Babayev, Minister of Economic Development of the Azerbaijan Republic.<br /><br />The award presentation ceremony was followed by concert program of State Symphonic Orchestra and soloist Murad Huseynov.</div>\r\n</div>', '2008-04-18', 1902, '', NULL, 0),
(1903, 'az', '', '', '2008-04-17', 1903, '', NULL, 0),
(1903, 'ru', '', '', '2008-04-17', 1904, '', NULL, 0),
(1903, 'en', 'ATIB member companies attend Azerbaijan-Greece Business Forum', '<div style="text-align: justify;">The Azerbaijan-Greece Business Forum organized by Greece Embassy was held in Baku, April 15, 2008. The forum brought together representatives of Azerbaijani and Greek Companies, specializing in production and selling of building machines and equipment, manufacturing and selling of leather and fur products, aluminum doors, windows, plates, and other areas. <br /><br />Olga Mezeridou, Economic Officer of Greek Embassy, Alakbar Mammadov, President of Azerbaijan Entrepreneurs Confederation, Emil Majidov, President of Azerbaijan Investment and Export Promotion Foundation spoke about the level of trade turnover, expansion of commercial relations and implementation of joint projects. <br /><br />''AtaHolding ASC'', ''AKAT İnşaat'', ''Aqrarkredit'', ''AtaBank'', ''AtaSənaye'', ''TAİS İKF'' from Azerbaijan Turkey Business Association as well as ''Gilan Holding'', ''Matanat A'', ''Karvan-L'', ''Repharma'', ''Khayal Holding'', ''Sirus Construction'', ''Fidanfarma'', ''Alfamed'', ''Zygon Caspian Consulting'', ''Nurgun Group'', ''Azerbaijan Investment Company'', ''Caspian Integration Business Club'' held bilateral meetings with Greece companies represented by ''Kronos'', ''Emek Group'', ''Kleva'', ''Mavrogiannakis'', ''Alumil Milonas'', ''D.Anastasiadis'', ''Voulis Chemicals'', and ''GEK SA''.</div>', '2008-04-17', 1905, '', NULL, 0),
(1906, 'az', '', '', '2008-04-10', 1906, '', NULL, 0),
(1906, 'ru', '', '', '2008-04-10', 1907, '', NULL, 0),
(1906, 'en', 'ATIB Chairman visits the USA', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Ahmet Erentok, Chairman of ATIB Executive Board visited the USA, April 1-3, 2008. During his visit, Mr. Erentok attended numerous meeting that were targeted to follow-up ATIB''s conference in December of 2007 and to discuss the forward actions of 2008. He met with the Ambassador of the Republic of Turkey to the USA, H.E. Nabi Sensoy, Research Director, Central Asia-Caucasus Institute of John Hopkins University, Svante Cornell, Chairman of US-Azeri Network (USAN), Adil Baghirov, Director of US Chamber of Commerce on Eurasian Affairs, Mike Considine and Deputy Director, Duygu Erdemgil, the President-Elect of the Assembly of Turkish-US Associations, Tom Neumann, Acting Director of Jewish Institute on National Security Affairs and Yola Johnston in charge of Projects, Executive Director of USACC, Mahir Iskender and lobbyist, Lydia Borland.<br /><br />On December 10, 2007, a joint effort between, ATIB, Eurasia Policy Center of Hudson Institute and Central Asia-Caucasus Institute of John Hopkins University held the first of its kind trilateral conference; &lsquo;Azerbaijan-Turkey-US relations and their importance for Eurasia'' in Washington, the series of meetings where the primary focus for planning of the next conference in Baku by the year end.<br /><br />The discussions also covered issues pertinent to current political affairs, the upcoming US presidential elections, ATIB''s activity and the importance of ATIB''s cooperation with US organizations, signing working Memorandum of Understanding with ATIB between USAN, ATAA and ASA and in depth conversations pertaining to the Azerbaijan Turkey History Research Foundation.</p>', '2008-04-10', 1908, '', NULL, 0),
(1909, 'az', '', '', '2008-04-07', 1909, '', NULL, 0),
(1909, 'ru', '', '', '2008-04-07', 1910, '', NULL, 0),
(1909, 'en', 'ATIB Members given an update from Committee for Management of State Property', '<p style="text-align: justify;">On April 4, 2008, Azerbaijan Turkey Business Association (ATIB) held a meeting for its members with Azer Bashirov, Deputy Chief of Attracting Investments and Privatization Division at State Committee for Management of State Property. Ali Ihsan Ghenj, ATIB Vice-chairman opened the meeting by welcoming the guest and participants and said it is the sixth seminar from a series of events organized in cooperation with state structures. Privatization is one of the important works in the restructuring process after independence of Azerbaijan.<br /><br />A.Bashirov gave a general overview about the history and activities of the committee. He spoke about the implementation of state programs on privatization of state property, management and protection of state property and attracting local and foreign investment. He said, about 40,000 small and 1,600 large-size enterprises have been privatized through tenders since the establishment of the committee. He gave Dashkesen Ore Dressing Plant &amp; Sumgait Industrial Production Enterprise as examples of the privatized enterprises. He also mentioned, investors should work not only to restore operational activities of the enterprise by contiuning to modernize the facility and to also, create a better working envioronment around human resources and future job opportunities within the privatization of the enterprise.<br /><br />Bashirov also mentioned that Turkish businessmen take an active part in the privatization process and play an important role in the improvement of the business climate in Azerbaijan.&nbsp;</p>', '2008-04-07', 1911, '', NULL, 0),
(1912, 'az', '', '', '2008-04-02', 1912, '', NULL, 0),
(1912, 'ru', '', '', '2008-04-02', 1913, '', NULL, 0),
(1912, 'en', 'Turkey''s ambassador to Azerbaijan visits ATIB office', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Newly appointed ambassador of Turkey to Azerbaijan Khulusi Kilich visited the office of the Azerbaijan Turkey Business Association on March 13, 2008. During the visit the diplomat met with members of ATIB Executive Board.<br /><br />Khulusi Kilich stressed importance of activity of Turkish businessmen in Azerbaijan and noted the association''s role in strengthening bilateral relations. He said Azerbaijan''s development is Turkey''s progress as well. The diplomat made a note in the memorial book of the association.</p>', '2008-04-02', 1914, '', NULL, 0),
(1915, 'az', '', '', '2008-03-03', 1915, '', NULL, 0),
(1915, 'ru', '', '', '2008-03-03', 1916, '', NULL, 0),
(1915, 'en', 'Next meeting of ATIB General Assembly held', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Next meeting of General Assembly of Azerbaijan Turkey Business Association (ATIB) was held on March 1, 2008. Besides ATIB members, representatives of Azerbaijan government, foreign embassies and international organizations partook at the event.<br /><br />According to the agenda, chairman of ATIB Executive Board Ahmet Erentok presented Annual Report 2007 to the meeting participants. The report was unanimously adopted by participants. Khayal Mammadli, chairman of Audit Commission presented the financial report of 2007 which was approved by meeting participants.<br /><br />New members were also elected to the Executive Board after resignation of some board members. Current composition of ATIB Executive Board includes the following members:<br /><br /></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">Ahmet Erentok (AtaHolding OJSC) - chairman of Executive Board</li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">Oruj Heydarov (AB standard OJSC) - vice-chairman of Executive Board</li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">Jemal Yanghin (Istanbul Charshi Import Export Ltd.) - vice-chairman of Executive Board</li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">Ali Ihsan Ghenj (Turquoise LLC) - vice-chairman of Executive Board</li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">Halim Atesh (Azercell Telecom LLC) - member of Executive Board</li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">Fatima Aslan (ATTAS PR/Anglo-American BS Alliances) - member of Executive Board</li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">Tayyar Shukurov (NJT 2000) - member of Executive Board</li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">Farhad Mehdiyev (Baku Innovation and Technologies Center) -member of Executive Board</li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">Rafail Shirinov (TAIS IKF) - member of Executive Board</li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">Akyil Imre (Saga Ghemi-Repair-Contrcution Company) member of Executive Board</li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">Ihsan Fatoglu (Fatoglu Istehsal Azerbaijan Ltd.) - member of Executive Board</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><br />New members were elected to Audit Board and the composition is as below:<br /><br /></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">Khayal Mammadkhanli (Complex Risk Solutions Consulting) - member of Audit commission</li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">Vugar Ismayilov (AzConsulting MMC) member of Audit Commission</li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">Kenan Kose (AKAT Inshaat MMC) - member of Audit Commission</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;"><br />Meeting participants also made a number of changes to ATIB Charter and approved ATIB Budget for 2008.&nbsp;</p>', '2008-03-03', 1917, '', NULL, 0),
(1918, 'az', '', '', '2008-02-13', 1918, '', NULL, 0),
(1918, 'ru', '', '', '2008-02-13', 1919, '', NULL, 0),
(1918, 'en', 'New appointment at ATIB Secretariat', '<p style="text-align: justify;">By the decision of ATIB Executive Board meeting on February 12, 2008, Rashad Rasoullu was appointed as Secretary General of Azerbaijan Turkey Business Association.<br /><br />Rashad Rasoullu graduated from International Economic Relations faculty of Azerbaijan State Economic Institute and received master''s decree on this major. In 2001-2002, he worked as Economic Researcher for Ayna/Zerkalo newspaper, and as a leading specialist in the Public Relations Department at the office of Executive Board of Azerbaijan National Bank in 2002-2004. Since 2004, Rashad Rasullu has been holding the post of Deputy Chairman of Supervisory Board at AtaHolding. Commencing his work as Advisor to ATIB Chairman in November of 2006, Rashad Rasullu was appointed Deputy Secretary General on March of 2007.<br /><br />Meanwhile Rashad Rasoullu has been working as a teacher in the International Relations Department of Azerbaijan Economic University and teaching the subjects on International Economic Relations, World Economy, International Marketing as well as study of local lore since 2005. He works on the scientific work &lsquo;Problems with Trans-nationalization of Azerbaijan''s Economy''.&nbsp;</p>', '2008-02-13', 1920, '', NULL, 0),
(1921, 'az', '', '', '2008-02-01', 1921, '', NULL, 0),
(1921, 'ru', '', '', '2008-02-01', 1922, '', NULL, 0),
(1921, 'en', 'ATIB members met representatives of Azerbaijan’s Ministry of Taxes', '<p style="text-align: justify;">Azerbaijan Turkey Business Association organized the meeting of ATIB members with Hamid Zeynalov, Deputy Chief of Tax Policy and Strategic Research Main Department and Shamil Arabov, chief of Legislation and Tax Administration Development Department of Taxes Ministry on February 1, 2008. The aim of the meeting was to inform ATIB members about recent amendments and changes to Tax Code of the Azerbaijan Republic and in general main directions of tax policy for near future.&nbsp; </p>\r\n<p>Addressing the event, ATIB Vice-chairman Ali Ihsan Ghenj spoke of ATIB&rsquo;s productive cooperation with state structures as well as Ministry of Taxes and cited the meeting as an example for this cooperation.</p>', '2008-02-01', 1923, '', NULL, 0),
(1924, 'az', 'ATİB sədri Ankarada mərhum prezident Heydər Əliyevə həsr olunmuş konfransda iştirak etdi', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><a href="http://atib.az/imagemanager/images/news/merhum.jpg"><img style="margin-left: 8px; margin-right: 8px; float: right;" src="http://atib.az/imagemanager/images/news/merhum_s.jpg" alt="" width="173" height="120" /></a>Dekabrın 13-də T&uuml;rkiyənin paytaxtı Ankarada "Heydər Əliyev d&uuml;nyasında mədəniyyət və sənət" m&ouml;vzusunda konfrans ke&ccedil;irilib. Azərbaycan və T&uuml;rkiyənin bir sıra d&ouml;vlət rəsmilərinin qatıldığı tədbirdə ATİB sədri Cemal Yangın iştirak edib.<br /><br /> Konfransda T&uuml;rkiyə C&uuml;mhuriyyətinin baş nazir m&uuml;avini Beşir Atalay, T&uuml;rkiyə C&uuml;mhuriyyəti B&ouml;y&uuml;k Millət Məclisinin sədri Cemil &Ccedil;i&ccedil;ek, Azərbaycan Respublikasının baş nazir m&uuml;avini El&ccedil;in Əfəndiyev, Azərbaycan Təhsil naziri Misir Mərdanov, T&uuml;rkiyə Təhsil naziri &Ouml;mer Din&ccedil;er, Azərbaycan Milli Elmlər Akademiyasının prezidenti Mahmud Kərimov Azərbaycanın T&uuml;rkiyədəki səfiri Faiq Bağırov və başqa rəsmi şəxslər nitqlər s&ouml;yləyiblər. Həm&ccedil;inin hər iki &ouml;lkənin parlament &uuml;zvləri, ali təhsil ocaqlarının təmsil&ccedil;iləri &ccedil;ıxışlar ediblər. &Ccedil;ıxış edənlər mərhum prezident Heydər Əliyevin mədəniyyət və sənət d&uuml;nyasına verdiyi &ouml;nəmdən, diqqət və qayğıdan danışıblar.</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>', '2012-12-13', 1924, '/Xəbərlər/merhum-1.jpg', '/Xəbərlər/main_13.12.2012.jpg', 0),
(1924, 'ru', '', '', '2012-12-13', 1925, '/Xəbərlər/merhum-1.jpg', '/Xəbərlər/main_13.12.2012.jpg', 0),
(1924, 'en', '', '', '2012-12-13', 1926, '/Xəbərlər/merhum-1.jpg', '/Xəbərlər/main_13.12.2012.jpg', 0),
(1927, 'az', 'ATİB “Zirvə Söhbətləri”nə başladı', '<p style="text-align: justify;"><img style="float: right; margin-left: 8px; margin-right: 8px;" src="http://atib.az/imagemanager/images/news/zirve-4_s.jpg" alt="" width="173" height="101" />Azərbaycan T&uuml;rkiyə İş Adamları Birliyi "Zirvə S&ouml;hbətləri" adı altında yeni tədbirlərə start verib. Bu g&ouml;r&uuml;şlərdə d&uuml;nyaca məşhur olan iş adamları, m&uuml;xtəlif sahələrin peşəkar m&uuml;təxəssiləri ATİB &uuml;zvləri ilə g&ouml;r&uuml;şəcək, seminar və təqdimatlar ke&ccedil;irəcək və &ouml;z uğur sirlərini b&ouml;l&uuml;şəcəklər. <br /><br /> "Zirvə S&ouml;hbətləri"-nin ilk qonağı T&uuml;rkiyənin məşhur insan qaynaqları eksperti, "insan m&uuml;həndisi" kimi tanınan cənab Ergun Zoga oldu. Dekabrın 14-də Excelsior oteldə ATİB &uuml;zvləri ilə ke&ccedil;irilən toplantıda Ergun Zoga "Yaşamak va hayatı anlamak" m&ouml;vzusunda təqdimat ke&ccedil;irdi.<br /><br /> Tədbirin əvvəllində ATİB sədri Cemal Yangın "Zirvə S&ouml;hbətləri" təşəbb&uuml;s&uuml; barədə məlumat verdi. O bildirdi ki, bu tədbirlərə dəvət ediləcək şəxslərin təcr&uuml;bəsi və onunla aparılan fikir m&uuml;badiləsi ATİB &uuml;zvlərinin gələcək fəaliyyətlərində daha b&ouml;y&uuml;k uğurlara imza atmasına yardım edəcək. Cemal Yangın qeyd etdi ki, Ergun Zoga həm d&ouml;vlət həm &ouml;zəl sektor &uuml;&ccedil;&uuml;n &ccedil;alışdığı uzun m&uuml;ddət ərzində b&ouml;y&uuml;k və uğurlu layihələrə imza atıb. Ergun Zoganın T&uuml;rkiyə daxilində və xaricdə verdiyi tədris, seminar və treyninqlərinin &uuml;mumi saatı 28 min saatdan &ccedil;oxdur. T&uuml;rkiyənin məşhur Ko&ccedil; Holdinqinin Treyninq və İnkişaf Mərkəzini (KOGEM) qurub və uzun m&uuml;ddət ona rəhbərlik edib. Hazırda insan qaynaqları &uuml;zrə T&uuml;rkiyə daxilində tədris-treyninq və eyni zamanda xaricdə seminarlar verməkdədir.<br /><br /> Sonra Ergun Zoga təqdimatı ke&ccedil;irdi. Təqdimatda insanın həyatı, d&uuml;ş&uuml;ncəsi, buna təsir edən bir sıra amillər, sevgi və formaları, ehtiyac, mənfəət, xarakter və s. barədə maraqlı məlumatlar təqdim olundu.<br /><br /> Tədqimatdan sonra şam yeməyi zamanı ATİB &uuml;zvləri Ergun Zoga ilə &uuml;nsiyyət imkanı qazandılar.<br /><br /></p>\r\n<table style="width: 100%;" border="0">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td style="width: 33%; text-align: center;"><a href="http://atib.az/imagemanager/images/news/zirve-1.jpg"><img src="http://atib.az/imagemanager/images/news/zirve-1_s.jpg" alt="" width="173" height="101" /></a></td>\r\n<td style="width: 33%; text-align: center;"><a href="http://atib.az/imagemanager/images/news/zirve-2.jpg"><img src="http://atib.az/imagemanager/images/news/zirve-2_s.jpg" alt="" width="173" height="101" /></a></td>\r\n<td style="width: 34%; text-align: center;"><a href="http://atib.az/imagemanager/images/news/zirve-3.jpg"><img src="http://atib.az/imagemanager/images/news/zirve-3_s.jpg" alt="" width="173" height="101" /></a></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: justify;">&nbsp;</p>', '2012-12-14', 1927, '/Xəbərlər/zirve-1.jpg', '/Xəbərlər/main_14.12.2012.jpg', 0),
(1927, 'ru', '', '', '2012-12-14', 1928, '/Xəbərlər/zirve-1.jpg', '/Xəbərlər/main_14.12.2012.jpg', 0),
